12.42	Cocamidopropyl_betaine	Cocamidopropyl betaine	Cocamidopropyl betaine is a synthetic surfactant derived from coconut oil and dimethylaminopropylamine. It is a zwitterionic chemical compound with a quaternary ammonium cation. It is a viscous pale yellow transparent liquid and is used as a surfactant in bath products such as shampoos and hand soaps, and in cosmetics as an emulsifying agent and thickener, and to reduce irritation purely ionic surfactants would cause. It also serves as an antistatic agent in hair conditioners.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Cocamidopropyl_betaine2.png/244px-Cocamidopropyl_betaine2.png
